Binary entry point (`cargo run --bin viz_data`) that generates `out/viz-data.json`, the data file consumed by the standalone `viz/index.html` tree viewer for browsing stroke categories down to full outlines and rendered snippets.

It orchestrates submodules rather than implementing logic itself: `comments::scan`/`scan_sections`/`scan_desc` extract `## label` markers, section boundaries, and descriptions from `dict.steno`'s raw text; `build::build` assembles the category/stroke tree from the fully-expanded `TypedEntry` list plus those marker maps; `json::to_json` serializes it. Categories are sourced strictly from explicit `## label` comments in `dict.steno` — ordinary prose comments are never treated as category markers, so adding a category requires adding that exact marker syntax upstream.

`root()` resolves the workspace root via `CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR` joined with `../..`, assuming this binary stays two directories below the workspace root (`crates/steno/src/bin/...`); relocating it breaks path resolution to `dict.steno` and `out/`. The dict source is loaded once and passed by reference to both the comment-scanning pass and `parse_source`/`expand_dict`, so the two stay in sync against the same string. All error paths collapse to `String` and get printed to stderr with `ExitCode::FAILURE`; no panics are expected on normal failure (missing file, parse error, expansion error). Output includes a summary line with category count, node count, and byte size of the written JSON, from `data.category_count()`/`node_count()`.